The paper proposes a computational framework that incorporates multimedia metrics into real-time bidding for display advertising. This involves analyzing contextual relevance, visual saliency, and ad memorability to improve users' ad experiences while maintaining benefits for publishers and advertisers. The paper's focus on multimedia metrics suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Additionally, the use of machine learning and optimization techniques to improve ad effectiveness and user experience suggests that it could also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision), or cs.DL (Machine Learning) categories.
